title.38: The Mutant Misadventures of Cloak and Dagger (1988) #18

description.5: She-Hulk's eagerness to see aliens is beset upon by both a professor and Spider-Man. What wackiness has Jen found herself in now?
description.14: Note: this issue contains only the Weapon X story by Barry Windsor-Smith. WEAPON X The Professor struggles to control Wolverine remotely. Cornelius demonstrates just how ""safe"" Logan is when he's deactivated.
description.16: Finally in possession of all the Infinity Stones, Thanos turns a stone golem into a powerful war machine.
description.17: The Sorcerer Supreme finds himself caught between ANOTHER devils' quarrel! Can Strange stop Mephisto and Satannish as they threaten existence yet again?
description.21: The Punisher must be held at bay against Taskmaster and Tombstone!
description.23: An unexpected friendship blossoms between the Hulk and Ajax. Betty Ross moves in with Marlo Chandler!
description.24: Tony Stark's darkest days are still ahead of him. Marrs Corporation attacks Stark Enterprises on Wall Street. Plus: Jim Rhodes and Tony Stark must help the Black Widow on a highly classified mission!
description.25: All of Thor's power, with Eric Masterson's mind! There's a new Thunder God in town, but will Eric have enough time to learn the ropes of being a hero before Ulik shows up to clean his clock?
description.29: The Time Variance Authority has placed the Fantastic Four under arrest! The charge? Crimes against synchronicity! Can the team prove their innocence to these brutal time cops?
description.30: The X-Men fight the Starjammers, who are Warskrulls in disguise. Inside their ship, Gambit helps the X-Men, while Lila Cheney and Deathbird locate the Warskrulls' matrix!
description.31: After a multitude of tests, we find Elsie Dee is not only packed with deadly explosives, but she also isn't human. At all. She is 100% android, yet Logan can't seem to let go…
description.37: Introducing the creepiest hero in the Marvel Universe as Rick Sheridan's life unravels thanks to the mysterious alien known as the Sleepwalker.
description.43: Sandman, one of Earth's Mightiest? Spider-Man and the Avengers trail an arms shipment after a tip from Sandman. But is the Avengers' new friend a man to be trusted?
description.44: Doctor Doom holds the Avengers and guests hostage at the gala for the Avengers Complex. What is Doom's motive behind the madness? Plus, Rage makes a mistake that could cost his teammates their lives!
description.45: When Bernie Rosenthal is kidnapped and held prisoner at the Lodge, the Watchdogs' "moral rehabilitation center," Captain America must put everything on the line to save her!
description.47: What if the Punisher killed Daredevil? During one of their battles, the Punisher tranquilizes Daredevil who accidentally falls to his death. This leads Frank Castle to become public enemy #1 with DD's close friend Spider-Man looking to bring the Punisher to justice.
description.51: Jen is a graduate of law school. But was there a class on making a deal with the devil? What faustian bargain does Mephisto have for She-Hulk?
description.53: Note: this issue contains only the Weapon X story by Barry Windsor-Smith.
description.54: Note: this issue contains only the Weapon X story by Barry Windsor-Smith.
description.56: The Silver Surfer races back to Earth to warn the other heroes of Thanos' diabolical master plan.
description.58: As Doctor Strange learns a horrifying truth about someone close to him, Baron Blood makes his move!
description.60: What if the heroes had lost Atlantis Attacks and Set had come to Earth? With many either dead or under the thrall of Set, Earth is likely doomed. And when the children of Set are born, that's endgame for Earth.
description.63: Taskmaster is looking mighty guilty for the murder of a neighborhood martial arts master! Who else could be to blame?
description.65: At the Pantheon's headquarters, Hulk dukes it out with the group's mightiest warrior...AJAX!
description.66: The invincible Iron Man and the Mandarin on a collision course! Iron Man recalls his origin in Southeast Asia. In the present, the Mandarin plots his conquest of China.
description.67: BROTHER VS. BROTHER! Thor and Loki clash with all their might, but in the heat of battle, Thor does the unthinkable! What will be the repercussions for Thor's forbidden actions? And will Eric be spared of them?
description.71: Fighting their way through, Castle Doom, the FF finally comes face to face with the mad doctor himself! Is this the final duel between Victor von Doom and Reed Richards at last?
description.72: Gambit tries to keep Jubilee quiet while they both hide from Professor X.  Jubilee and Lilandra are under Psylocke's control and they soon discover that they are pawns in a larger game.
description.73: A rough exterior, but a warm heart. Wolvie has always been known for his dual sides, but this time we see his good intentions may be used against him…
description.75: Grey Gargoyle and Shrike are contracted for a kill but She-Hulk's on the case and nobody dies today!
description.80: The Brattle Gun should never see the light of day, let alone be used. Punisher and Rose race against the clock to make sure it’s destroyed.
description.85: Spider-Man's on an island getaway...courtesy of Venom! Spidey will have to use all his cunning to defeat Brock once and for all. But will Venom fall for the ploy?
description.86: The Avengers throw a gala to celebrate the opening of the Avengers Complex. But when Doctor Doom makes a surprise appearance, the Avengers get more "fun" than they'd bargained for!
description.87: It's been a long time coming-Captain America wages war on the Watchdogs!
description.88: Note: this issue contains only the Weapon X story by Barry Windsor-Smith. WEAPON X After the truth-both about the program and Logan himself-is explained to Cornelius, will he want to stay on board with Project X?
description.90: The Silver Surfer must answer for sins from his past!
description.92: The menace of ZODIAK threatens the world of Doctor Strange, and he can't win this fight alone! Enter: GHOST RIDER!
description.94: Note: this issue contains only the Weapon X story by Barry Windsor-Smith. WEAPON X Cornelius and Hines may have bitten off more than they could chew when they chose Logan to be their subject. It's about time they find out what the Wolverine's been hiding in his wrists.
description.95: Matt Murdock eases back into his former life after squaring off with Bullet.
description.97: Vigilante Crazy Eight has been sentenced to death for the murder of a Senator! But only after her death does Doc Samson have a shocking revelation...
description.98: Tony Stark gets a blast from the past! After an intense battle against the villain Vibro, Iron Man must take a break from the spotlight, and reflect on his past. What will the Armored Avenger find deep in the far recesses of his memories?

0.text: In the Savage Land, violent skirmishes break out between the natives and the Rand Corporation team, as the exploration of the lost world begins. Meanwhile, the Punisher closes in on the drug-dealing Desmond Marrs!

1.text: The Syndicate gets a new member -- the SHOCKER! And it's up to Spider-Man to defuse an explosive situation before it's too late!

2.text: After nearly dying, Moon Knight rushes to stop Stained Glass Scarlet!

3.text: Super-sized special! Just as her romantic tension with Nightcrawler reaches a boiling point, someone beyond the grave possesses the shape-shifting Meggan! Which unrestful ghost has claimed the changeling for themselves? Excalibur has never faced a supernatural foe quite like this one…and the team must play entirely by the sinister spirit’s rules!

4.text: Edifice Rex…or Edifice Wrecks? A cosmically charged neat freak is too overzealous in his clean-up of Earth. Is such a thing possible? Damage Control thinks so!

5.text: She-Hulk's eagerness to see aliens is beset upon by both a professor and Spider-Man. What wackiness has Jen found herself in now?

7.text: Ghost Rider, Johnny Blaze, H.E.A.R.T., Blackout, and Deathwatch go toe-to-toe in Central Park!

8.text: Who is the enigmatic Portal, and why does his armor look so familiar? Will he be ally or enemy to Darkhawk?

9.text: If the Guardians cannot prevent the creation of Korvac, their universe will end!

10.text: The Surfer--with the power of the Quantum Bands-battles the Guardians of the Galaxy. Plus, Galactus retells the story of Silver Surfer's creation.

11.text: SPIRIT OF VENGEANCE PART 2 The Guardians face off against the Spirit of Vengeance! Plus, the Universal Church rears its ugly head!

12.text: THE SOULS OF CYBER-FOLK PART 1 Guest-starring the X-Man, Forge! Deathlok squares off with the Capturebots after Forge and Misty Knight are nearly kidnapped. Why are the Capturebots after cyborgs? And will Deathlok and Misty Knight be able to save Forg

13.text: FOREVER YESTERDAY PART 3 Nova faces the disastrous fallout from his battle with the Avengers and X-Men. The fury of Sphinx reaches a searing new height. In the conclusion to Forever Yesterday, will the New Warriors at long last return to their own time?

14.text: Note: this issue contains only the Weapon X story by Barry Windsor-Smith.

15.text: Spider-Man’s Canadian adventure continues as he and Wolverine face off against the Wendigo!

16.text: Finally in possession of all the Infinity Stones, Thanos turns a stone golem into a powerful war machine.

17.text: The Sorcerer Supreme finds himself caught between ANOTHER devils' quarrel! Can Strange stop Mephisto and Satannish as they threaten existence yet again?

18.text: It's the return of the super hero poker game as Nick Fury, the Thing, Mr. Fantastic and Captain America play for high stakes against the Mandarin.

20.text: Johnny Blaze has set a trap for Danny Ketch in the hopes of vanquishing the spirit that has haunted him for most of his life!

22.text: U.K. vs. U.S.A.! Excalibur is too distracted in battle with the West Coast Avengers to notice that Doctor Doom has obtained an unlimited source of energy!

27.text: Apocalypse strengthens his reign by seizing the Inhumans’ refuge on the moon!

31.text: After a multitude of tests, we find Elsie Dee is not only packed with deadly explosives, but she also isn't human. At all. She is 100% android, yet Logan can't seem to let go…

33.text: Darkhawk takes on a new foe in the form of Savage Steel! Also, secrets of Darkhawk's amulet will be revealed!

34.text: SPIRIT OF VENGEANCE PART 1 The arrival of the Spirit of Vengeance in the 31st century could mean the end of Starhawk.

35.text: FOREVER YESTERDAY PART 2 The Sphinx has re-written all of reality using the Ka stone. The Warriors find themselves fighting the Egyptian versions of the Avengers and X-Men. But even in the Sphinx’s new world, the Warriors find that mutants are still denied personal rights.

36.text: Featuring the New Warriors, Spider-Man and Hulk! Damage Control is under PR fire when accused of staging disasters for the sake of business.

37.text: Introducing the creepiest hero in the Marvel Universe as Rick Sheridan's life unravels thanks to the mysterious alien known as the Sleepwalker.

39.text: The Sub-Mariner goes SAVAGE…in the SAVAGE LAND! Desmond Marrs reaches a new level of discontent over his sister dating Namor!

41.text: The Sinister Syndicate is finally ready to face off against Spider-Man! Even the Wall-Crawler is going to struggle against five-on-one odds!

42.text: New York City is on the brink of disaster and Moon Knight is the only one who can save the city!

46.text: The West Coast Avengers have to prevent a second coming of Pearl Harbor!

48.text: Wendell may have lost his physical form, but he can still exist as a quantum being! Ghost Rider guest-stars to serve a dish of cold revenge to Deathurge for Quasar’s “death”! Maelstrom puts his next move into play…

51.text: Jen is a graduate of law school. But was there a class on making a deal with the devil? What Faustian bargain does Mephisto have in mind for She-Hulk?

53.text: Note: this issue contains only the Weapon X story by Barry Windsor-Smith.

54.text: Note: this issue contains only the Weapon X story by Barry Windsor-Smith.

55.text: Wolverine is the best there is at what he does, but Spider-Man is pretty good too!

56.text: The Silver Surfer races back to Earth to warn the other heroes of Thanos' diabolical master plan.

57.text: Red Skull’s spy-ring is discovered within S.H.I.E.L.D.’s inner ranks, but even more pertinent information is missing. Where is Hydra’s nuclear submarine? And will Nick Fury and company uncover the location all too late?

58.text: As Doctor Strange learns a horrifying truth about someone close to him, Baron Blood makes his move!

59.text: The West Coast Avengers are met with their first real challenge in quite a while, courtesy of The Pacific Overlords, a new super-villian team consisting of Jawbreaker, Kuroko, Taifu and others!

61.text: Maelstrom recruits the Weird Sisters to run a full diagnostic on the Quantum-Bands. Meanwhile, Quasar has been hung up to dry…and to perish.

64.text: Featuring the West Coast Avengers and Doctor Doom! The FF’s most malignant foe requests Excalibur’s aid to obtain a new super weapon.

69.text: Nathan Summers is kidnapped by a mysterious woman during a battle.

73.text: A rough exterior, but a warm heart. Wolvie has always been known for his dual sides, but this time we see his good intentions may be used against him…

75.text: Grey Gargoyle and Shrike are contracted for a kill but She-Hulk's on the case and nobody dies today!

77.text: The trial of the Sub-Mariner comes to a close, and the verdict is in! Plus, Namor has it out with the Griffin; his relationship with Phoebe Marrs heats up; the Fantastic Four is still hanging around; Ka-Zar and Danny (Iron Fist) Rand arrive in the Savage Land; Desmond Marrs starts dealing drugs.

78.text: A Spidey story…as remembered by the villains! The Beetle is back, and he's joining forces with some of Spidey's most notorious foes -- Rhino! Boomerang! Hydro-Man! Speed Demon! Introducing the SINISTER SYNDICATE!

79.text: Someone from Moon Knight's past is painting the city scarlet with the blood of innocents.

81.text: Darkhawk's inaugural team-up rages on as he and Spidey battle the Hobgoblin!

82.text: The Guardians respond to a distress call on the other side of the Galaxy and encounter a foe there with strength that rivals that of Firelord, Protector of the Universe!

83.text: FOREVER YESTERDAY PART 1 The New Warriors hurtled back in time! Or is it the present? The team finds themselves in an alternate future where the fall of ancient Egypt never occurred. Meet Captain Assyria, the new ruler of the Avengers!

84.text: Ghost Rider hunts down a drug dealer named Snowblind on the streets of Brooklyn!

88.text: Note: this issue contains only the Weapon X story by Barry Windsor-Smith.

89.text: The Amazing Spider-Man and the Savage Wolverine combat the carnivorous Wendigo!

90.text: The Silver Surfer must answer for sins from his past!

92.text: The menace of ZODIAK threatens the world of Doctor Strange, and he can't win this fight alone! Enter: GHOST RIDER!

93.text: Baron Strucker, back from the dead! A new face of Hydra is forming, and it all traces back to Fury’s oldest nemesis. The Red Skull plots an attack against a weakened S.H.I.E.L.D.

94.text: Note: this issue contains only the Weapon X story by Barry Windsor-Smith.

96.text: Silver Sable and her Wild Pack don’t stand a chance against Cap Britain’s Excalibur! Or maybe we’ve spoken too soon…?

99.text: When the New Mutants hear strange noises emanating from the Danger Room, they investigate. Who is the mysterious warrior destroying all of their equipment? Plus, the face of Stryfe revealed!
